  "prompt": "Where can I download free pdf books for mechanical engineering?",
  "response": "There are several reputable sources where you can find free PDF books on mechanical engineering. Here are a few options:\n\n1. **Project Gutenberg**: Offers over 60,000 free eBooks, including some engineering texts. Visit [Project Gutenberg](https://www.gutenberg.org/) and search for mechanical engineering-related titles.\n\n2. **Open Library**: A part of the Internet Archive, this site provides access to millions of books, including various engineering textbooks. Check out [Open Library](https://openlibrary.org/) and search for mechanical engineering books.\n\n3. **Google Scholar**: You can find a range of academic papers and some books related to mechanical engineering. Go to [Google Scholar](https://scholar.google.com/) and search for specific topics or authors.\n\n4. **Engineering Books**: Websites like [Free-Ebooks.net](https://www.free-ebooks.net/) offer a section dedicated to engineering, where you might find useful resources.\n\n5. **Online University Repositories**: Some universities provide access to free course materials and textbooks. Look for engineering departments of universities that may share resources online.\n\n6. **Library Genesis**: Although somewhat controversial, sites like Library Genesis can offer access to a large database of books, including many textbooks. Search for mechanical engineering titles there.\n\n7. **Bookboon**: This site offers a range of free textbooks specifically for engineering students. Visit [Bookboon](https://bookboon.com/) and navigate to the engineering section.\n\nAlways ensure you are accessing content legally and in accordance with copyright laws.",
